[We are grateful for this measured official response, and particularly for
the information on the follow up lab results. Given the repeated
introduction of dengue into Hawaii by people incubating the virus, we fear
that it is only a matter of time before there is an outbreak there --
unless the widespread use of air conditioning
leads to the 'Tex/Mex effect,' whereby dengue hasn't (so far) become
established north of the Mexican border, despite its occurrence right up to
there.
We would be interested to hear what mosquito control measures are being
taken in Hawaii. - Mod.JW
